---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Bronson Harrington — Organic Authority & Credibility Infrastructure">

  <!-- ============================================================
       HERO — Pattern interrupt. Name the fear first.
  ============================================================ -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow fade-up">Organic Authority · Due Diligence · Growth Architecture</p>
      <h1 class="fade-up fade-up-delay-1">
        Your web presence<br/>
        is the first thing<br/>
        they check<span class="accent">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub fade-up fade-up-delay-2">
        Most Web3 projects, iGaming operators, and funded startups fail that check —
        not because the product is weak, but because the digital footprint
        looks like it was built over a weekend.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions fade-up fade-up-delay-3">
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-accent">Run a free audit</a>
        <a href="#method" class="btn">See the method</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider container-divider"></div>

  <!-- ============================================================
       INSIDER SPECIFICITY — Three verticals, surgical observations
  ============================================================ -->
  <section id="work" class="verticals">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Who I work with</p>
      <div class="verticals-grid">

        <div class="vertical-card">
          <span class="vertical-num accent">01</span>
          <h3>Web3 &amp; Crypto</h3>
          <p>A project with strong tokenomics and a thin organic footprint reads as a rug pull to anyone who Googles it. Pre-launch credibility architecture changes that before the first investor call.</p>
          <span class="vertical-tag">Pre-launch · Token listings · DAO legitimacy</span>
        </div>

        <div class="vertical-card">
          <span class="vertical-num accent">02</span>
          <h3>iGaming Operators</h3>
          <p>Entering a new market means passing three layers of scrutiny simultaneously — regulators, affiliates, and players. Your organic presence either opens those doors or closes them before you knock.</p>
          <span class="vertical-tag">Market entry · Licensing · Affiliate trust</span>
        </div>

        <div class="vertical-card">
          <span class="vertical-num accent">03</span>
          <h3>Startups &amp; Founders</h3>
          <p>Investors run two searches before the meeting: your name, and your company. If neither returns authoritative signals, the meeting already has a headwind. Fix that before the deck goes out.</p>
          <span class="vertical-tag">Fundraising · Partner trust · Brand authority</span>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider container-divider"></div>

  <!-- ============================================================
       METHOD — The three-layer system made visible
  ============================================================ -->
  <section id="method" class="method">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">The method</p>
      <h2>Three layers.<br/>One outcome<span class="accent">.</span></h2>
      <p class="method-intro">
        Most agencies sell outputs — a site, some content, a ranking report.
        I build the underlying architecture that makes a brand survive scrutiny.
        Every engagement moves through three sequential layers.
      </p>

      <div class="layers">

        <div class="layer">
          <div class="layer-header">
            <span class="layer-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Foundation</h3>
              <span class="layer-sub">Design · Technical SEO · Site architecture</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>Does this brand look and function like a legitimate operation? Brand design, Core Web Vitals, crawl architecture, schema, and technical health — the baseline every other layer depends on.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="layer-connector" aria-hidden="true">
          <span>↓</span>
        </div>

        <div class="layer">
          <div class="layer-header">
            <span class="layer-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Authority Build</h3>
              <span class="layer-sub">Topical authority · Content architecture · Entity SEO</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>Can this brand be found, cited, and trusted by search engines — and by the humans behind them? Organic growth built on topical depth, not volume. The kind of authority that reads as expertise, not optimization.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="layer-connector" aria-hidden="true">
          <span>↓</span>
        </div>

        <div class="layer layer-highlight">
          <div class="layer-header">
            <span class="layer-num accent">03</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Due Diligence Signal</h3>
              <span class="layer-sub">Investor-grade presence · Regulatory footprint · Partner trust</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>Does this brand survive a sceptical third-party Google search? Layer three is the output of everything below it — a web presence that passes the informal due diligence that happens before every deal, deposit, and partnership.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider container-divider"></div>

  <!-- ============================================================
       ABOUT — Identity, authority markers, 25 years compressed
  ============================================================ -->
  <section id="about" class="about">
    <div class="container about-inner">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p class="section-label">About</p>
        <h2>25 years in<br/>rooms where<br/>trust is the<br/>product<span class="accent">.</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-body">
        <p>
          I've spent the better part of two and a half decades building organic growth systems
          for finance brands, iGaming operators, and digital businesses where credibility
          isn't a marketing concern — it's an operational one.
        </p>
        <p>
          That background means I understand what's actually at stake when a Web3 project
          goes to market with a thin footprint, or an iGaming operator enters a regulated
          jurisdiction with no organic authority signals. I've seen what it costs.
        </p>
        <p>
          I work with a small number of clients at a time — typically three or four —
          because the work demands the kind of attention you can't distribute across
          a full agency roster.
        </p>
        <div class="about-markers">
          <div class="marker">
            <span class="marker-num accent">25+</span>
            <span>Years in organic growth</span>
          </div>
          <div class="marker">
            <span class="marker-num accent">3–4</span>
            <span>Clients at a time</span>
          </div>
          <div class="marker">
            <span class="marker-num accent">iGaming</span>
            <span>Finance · Web3 · Startups</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider container-divider"></div>

  <!-- ============================================================
       CTA — Assessor framing, scarcity, no pressure
  ============================================================ -->
  <section id="contact" class="contact">
    <div class="container contact-inner">
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <h2>Before the meeting,<br/>know where you stand<span class="accent">.</span></h2>
      <p>
        I offer a free due diligence scan of your web presence — the same assessment
        a cautious investor or regulator would run informally before engaging.
        No pitch. No proposal. Just an honest read of what your digital footprint
        is currently signalling.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:gnuboss@gmail.com?subject=Free%20Audit%20Request" class="btn btn-accent">
        Request the free audit
      </a>
      <div class="contact-alt">
        <a href="tel:+50661825718" class="contact-link">+506 6182 5718</a>
        <span class="muted">·</span>
        <a href="https://wa.me/50661825718?text=Hi%20Bronson%2C%20I'd%20like%20to%20request%20a%20free%20audit" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="contact-link">WhatsApp</a>
      </div>
      <p class="contact-note muted">
        Response within 48 hours. I take on new clients when capacity allows.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
/* ---- Hero ---- */
.hero {
  padding: clamp(4rem, 10vw, 8rem) 0 clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem);
}

.hero-eyebrow {
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.hero h1 {
  margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
}

.hero-sub {
  font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.15rem);
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
}

.hero-actions {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

/* ---- Dividers ---- */
.container-divider {
  max-width: var(--max-w);
  padding: 0 clamp(1.25rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  margin: 0 auto;
}

/* ---- Section labels ---- */
.section-label {
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  max-width: none;
}

/* ---- Verticals ---- */
.verticals-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
  gap: 2px;
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.vertical-card {
  padding: 2.5rem 2rem;
  border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
  transition: background 0.2s;
}

.vertical-card:last-child { border-right: none; }
.vertical-card:hover { background: var(--paper-warm); }

.vertical-num {
  display: block;
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.vertical-card h3 {
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.vertical-card p {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
}

.vertical-tag {
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
}

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .verticals-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .vertical-card  { border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .vertical-card:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
}

/* ---- Method ---- */
.method-intro {
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  margin: 1.5rem 0 3rem;
  font-size: 1rem;
}

.layers {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0;
}

.layer {
  padding: 2.25rem 2rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-bottom: none;
}

.layer:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }

.layer-highlight {
  background: var(--paper-warm);
}

.layer-header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.layer-num {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  font-weight: 300;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
  flex-shrink: 0;
  padding-top: 2px;
}

.layer-sub {
  display: block;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
  margin-top: 0.3rem;
}

.layer p {
  font-size: 0.92rem;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  padding-left: calc(1.1rem + 1.5rem);
}

.layer-connector {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  height: 2.5rem;
  color: var(--accent);
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
  background: var(--paper);
}

/* ---- About ---- */
.about-inner {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.4fr;
  gap: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 5rem);
  align-items: start;
}

.about-body p {
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}

.about-markers {
  display: flex;
  gap: 2.5rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  padding-top: 2rem;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.marker {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.25rem;
}

.marker-num {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 1.6rem;
  font-weight: 300;
  line-height: 1;
}

.marker span:last-child {
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
}

@media (max-width: 700px) {
  .about-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}

/* ---- Contact ---- */
.contact-inner {
  max-width: 620px;
}

.contact h2 { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

.contact p {
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}

.contact-note {
  margin-top: 1.25rem;
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

.contact-alt {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  margin-top: 1.25rem;
  font-size: 0.82rem;
}

.contact-link {
  color: var(--ink-muted);
  transition: color 0.2s;
  letter-spacing: 0.03em;
}

.contact-link:hover { color: var(--accent); }
</style>
